<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">550 E 1/111</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Italian Embassy</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum</hi></p>
                        <p>Owing to the protracted crisis of the Italian Cabinet, the Royal
                            Government has found itself in the impossibility of maintaining
                            unchanged the date of March 8th chosen by the Supreme Council for the
                            Genoa Conference.</p>
                        <pb facs="0512" n="392" xml:id="pg_392"/>
                        <p>The Italian Government has therefore been compelled to postpone the
                            convening of the Conference and to communicate such a decision to every
                            Government invited to said Conference.</p>
                        <p>The Italian Government will get in touch with every Allied Government in
                            order to choose of one accord a new date.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline rendition="#left">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-26"><hi rend="italic">February 26, 1922</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>